<br>
While i havent had anybody say anything negative to me about it, but i just figure the people that might have a problem are keeping quiet.   I'm curious of how you would base your judgement on somebody who did this.  Just for the record, your more than likely not gonna change my already-made-up-opinion on the matter, but i am curious to see your perspective.  thx. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/24/01 4:11:34 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/DAoC/lynxhead.jpg WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=116></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do you frown on this?</span><hr size=1> Well to me, farming is when a person who gets no benefits from camping a specific mob do it just to get its loot to sell for money.  For example, a 55th lvl druid camping the ancient croc for the gatorscale leggings of sleeves because it's an easy spawn and the item can still be sold fairly easily.  At 55th one would assume that he has significantly better items than gatorscale legs or arms.<br>
<br>
Merchanting is when you have things in your bank that you don't need, friends don't need, twinks don't need, guild don't need, and it's just taking up space, so why not sell them to someone who can use it and make some money?  <br>
<br>
Although my opinion on farming doesn't really apply to DAoC since you can't farm mobs you don't get exp out of, but I don't really see anything wrong with what you're doing, Broomhilda.  You're in Mithra gaining experience and getting loot.  You're killing the mobs for a reason, exp, and loot just so happens to be a result as well, so why not sell what you don't need?  <br>
<br>
If you're feeling generous and feel like donating your loot to another player, then great!  But if not, you have every right to sell your loot.  I can understand that you need money too.  You have needs too. :) <p><CENTER>
