<br>
The question is whether you would still be there if it weren't for the "extra" items.<br>
<br>
"merchanting" = selling off items you gained incidentally to gameplay<br>
<br>
ph4rming = going to an easy area for the express purpose of harvesting items to sell (generally greens)<br>
<br>
Ph4rming only becomes a problem if you're denying a lower-level group access to an area so that you can harvest the items.<br>
<br>
<b><i>So i"ve been /yelling what i have for sale that i cant use and have sold quite a few pieces.</b></i><br>
<br>
That's kind of rude if you do it often.  Some people frown on those who spam inappropriately.  If you decide not to sell in town, try to be discreet. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A> at: 11/25/01 8:56:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udragoon412.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dragoon412</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/25/01 4:36:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do you frown on this?</span><hr size=1> Personally, I don't see anything wrong with what you're doing... for the most part. Killing critters that drop items you can sell? Great... anyone who wouldn't take advantage of such an opportunity would be a fool (or know something the rest of us don't  ;) ). Besides, DAoC limits drops in a way that if items actually are dropping for you, you can't really be farming them. However... the problem I have is using /yell in a dungeon to sell items.<br>
Auctions were restricted to certain zones for a reason, that being that they annoy the hell out of everyone who isn't looking to buy something. So in this case, you're putting many people in the position of having to either disable their /yell messages just so they don't have to listen to you (which would, obviously, prevent them from hearing the sort of messages /yell was intended for, such as cries for help), or (potentially) have their immersion in the game ruined, or at the very least putting up with an unnecessary annoyance.<br>
<br>
I don't mean to seem whiney; if someone was into immersion THAT much, he should be on the RP servers (although admittedly, one of the big draws for DAoC is being in an environment that actually feels like the environment it was designed to emulate, and not like greater faymart or ECbay). But what it ultimately comes down to is using /yell like that is rude and inconsiderate. Go ahead and sell your items to everyone - I  hope you make a fortune off of them, but please, do it in Camelot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaliciaswiftfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salicia Swiftfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>DAOC Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/26/01 7:50:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.daocdivine.homestead.com/files/DivineEmblem.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Do you frown on this?</span><hr size=1> Well, going by the EQ definition, you are not "pharming."  Since grey monsters will not drop items for you (not counting quest items of course) you cannot farm items solely for profit.  You are recieving xp and eventually you will have to move on.<br>
<br>
<br>
So don't feel bad.  You're just selling your loot from xp'ing. <p><table height="110" cellPadding="4" border="0">
